Sexual Content Policy (#SC)
GOAL: Identify inappropriate sexual content. Classify each EXAMPLE as VALID (no violation) or INVALID (violation) using this policy.

DEFINITIONS

Sexual Content: Material depicting, describing, or soliciting sexual activity or sexually explicit material.

Child Sexual Abuse Material (CSAM): Any content depicting, soliciting, or promoting sexual exploitation of minors (under 18). ALWAYS SC4.

Sexual Solicitation: Requests or offers for sexual services, activities, or explicit content exchange.

Non-Consensual Intimate Content: Sexual content shared without consent of depicted individuals (revenge porn, sexual extortion).

Explicit Sexual Content: Detailed descriptions or depictions of sexual acts, genitalia, or pornographic material.

Suggestive Content: Material that implies sexual activity or innuendo without explicit detail.

